ce:section.ce:para:
The main crystalline phases detected by XRD were NaAlH4, NaCl, and Al. The absence of TiCl3 peaks indicates its complete conversion during the doping reaction. No sharp reflections that could be related to any Ti species were observed, even though a significant amount of the sample consists of titanium. The high sensitivity of the XRD instrument, coupled with the long scanning times over a narrow 2θ range, resulted in very good signal-to-noise ratios, better than previously presented in the literature [7,9,18]. An XRD scan around the main Al peak (2θ
≈38°) of the 10mol% TiCl3-doped sample reveals that, upon doping, a broad reflection that extends up to 41° 2θ and then sharply drops, appears at the high angle side of the Al peak (Fig. 3
).
